.Dd April 8, 2004
.Dt MBSINIT 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm mbsinit
.Nd "determine conversion object status"
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libc
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In wchar.h
.Ft int
.Fn mbsinit "const mbstate_t *ps"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn mbsinit
function determines whether the
.Vt mbstate_t
object pointed to by
.Fa ps
describes an initial conversion state.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
The
.Fn mbsinit
function returns non-zero if
.Fa ps
is
.Dv NULL
or describes an initial conversion state,
otherwise it returns zero.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr mbrlen 3 ,
.Xr mbrtowc 3 ,
.Xr mbsrtowcs 3 ,
.Xr multibyte 3 ,
.Xr wcrtomb 3 ,
.Xr wcsrtombs 3
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Fn mbsinit
function conforms to
.St -isoC-99 .
